Apartheid-era laws aren't in themselves necessarily wrong, but it's the way they're used that could be a problem according to Freedom Under Law's Nicole Fritz. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - Apartheid-era laws aren't in themselves necessarily wrong, but it's the way they're used that could be a problem according to Freedom Under Law's Nicole Fritz. READ: ANC oppressing black people with apartheid laws: EFF After a court dismissed EFF Leader Julius Malema's bid to challenge the constitutionality of the Riotous Assemblies Act of 1956, the president of the Red Berets plans to appeal the matter in the Constitutional Court. Fritz said the way the laws were used but the definitions they were drafted under are not necessarily unconstitutional.